      "level": {
        "value": 14
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> Zon-Kuthon's gift to Kazavon — an ashmede assassin-enforcer. The night of the raid she was decoyed out of the castle by <strong>Kleestad's false-treason ploy</strong>; she returned too late, failed to retake Scarwall, and was scavenging in the tower when Mandraivus died — so the rising curse seized <em>her</em> soul as an anchor (D14). She monitors the PCs' progress through gargoyle reports, invisible imps, and the telepathy of her last devils (D12 barbed pair, D18 bone pair) — as each falls, the survivors are ordered back to her side. Aura of fear (@Check[type:will|dc:31] or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.TBSHQspnbcqxsmjL]{Frightened 1}, cowering 1 round on a critical failure).</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
